Hi Matthew.

To put it simply all Contacts are Visitors but not all Visitors are Contacts.

A visitor is anyone who visits the site. The system gathers information about all visitors including anonymous ones, but this can be very limited information such as simply a unique ID for a visit if no cookie has been accepted by the visitor.&#x20;

A contact is a visitor who is identified by a cookie. Activities on a site tracked by cookies gets associated to a contact via the visitors GUID.&#x20;

From looking at the source code it looks as though VisitorToContactVisitorGUID is used to map a visitor's activity to a contact.

For more information about visitors, contacts, and cookies, please take a look at our documentation on the subject here: <https://docs.kentico.com/business-users/digital-marketing/contact-management>
